1. Introduction
Welcome to JobSpot ("we", "our", "us"). We are committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application ("App"). Please read this policy carefully to understand our views and practices regarding your personal data and how we will treat it.

2. Information We Collect
We may collect and process the following data about you:

2.1 Personal Information:

Name
Email address
Phone number
Date of birth
Gender
Employment history
Educational background
Resume and cover letter
2.2 Device Information:

Device type
Operating system version
IP address
Unique device identifiers
Mobile network information
2.3 Usage Data:

Log-in details
Search history
Job application history
Interaction with advertisements
App usage patterns
3. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect in the following ways:

3.1 To Provide and Improve Our Services:

Matching job seekers with relevant job opportunities
Customizing and personalizing your experience
Enhancing app functionality and user experience
3.2 To Communicate with You:

Sending notifications about job opportunities
Responding to your inquiries and requests
Providing customer support
3.3 For Marketing and Promotional Activities:

Sending newsletters, promotions, and special offers
Conducting surveys and feedback requests
3.4 For Legal and Security Purposes:

Complying with legal obligations
Protecting the rights, property, or safety of [Job App Name], our users, and the public
4. How We Share Your Information
We do not sell or trade your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your information with:

4.1 Service Providers:

Third-party vendors who provide services on our behalf (e.g., hosting, data analysis, payment processing)
4.2 Legal Requirements:

If required by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., court orders, government regulations)
4.3 Business Transfers:

In connection with any merger, sale of company assets, or acquisition, your information may be transferred as part of the transaction.
5. Your Rights and Choices
You have the following rights regarding your personal data:

5.1 Access and Correction:

You can access and update your personal information through your account settings.
5.2 Deletion:

You can request the deletion of your account and personal data by contacting us at [Insert Contact Information].
5.3 Restriction and Objection:

You can restrict or object to the processing of your personal data under certain circumstances.
5.4 Data Portability:

You can request a copy of your personal data in a structured, machine-readable format.
6. Data Security
We implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information. However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Effective Date" at the top. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

